  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want it to be possible to sign a transaction with minimum gas price and gas limit\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Can't sign or cancel a transaction after decreasing gas price or gas limit to minimum. User stays on the Send transaction screen without any warning or error\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTransaction is signed after clicking Sign transaction button or cancelled after clicking Cancel button\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAfter clicking Cancel or Sign transaction button user stays on the Send transaction screen - transaction is neither canceled not signed. No error is shown also\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Naivgate ot Wallet tab\r\n- Tap Send transaction button\r\n- Specify a recipient\r\n- Select STT as an asset\r\n- Type 20 in the amount field\r\n- Click Advanced button\r\n- Set gas limit to `0.00000000000000000001` and/or gas price to `0.00000000000000000001` (20 digits after .)\r\n- Click Sign transaction\r\n- Input your password\r\n- Try clicking Cancel and Sign transaction buttons\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.21 (6121) node a339d7e\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
